## üß† Today‚Äôs Practice Tasks:

### 1. Personal Profile Webpage
Create a full HTML page that includes:
- A `<title>`: `My Profile`
- `<h1>`: Your Name (center it using CSS)
- A paragraph about yourself
  - Style the text color using `style` attribute
- Add a **link** to your favorite YouTube channel
  - Opens in a new tab (`target="_blank"`)
- Use formatting tags like `<b>`, `<i>`, `<u>`, `<mark>` inside the paragraph
- Add a horizontal line `<hr>` between sections
- Add one HTML comment in the code

---

### 2. Color & Text Style Showcase
Create a new HTML file that:
- Has 3 paragraphs, each with different text colors:
  - Use one named color (e.g., `red`)
  - One HEX color (e.g., `#00ff00`)
  - One RGB color (e.g., `rgb(0,0,255)`)
- Use inline CSS (`style`) to:
  - Change font size (e.g., `20px`)
  - Make one paragraph bold and another italic
- Use a heading styled with:
  - Background color
  - White text color

---

### 3. HTML + Internal CSS Practice
- Create a webpage titled `CSS Practice`
- Use internal CSS with `<style>` tag inside `<head>`
- Style all `<h1>` elements:
  - Color: Purple
  - Text-align: Center
- Style all `<p>` elements:
  - Font size: `18px`
  - Text color: Blue
  - Background color: Light gray (`#f0f0f0`)
- Add a styled link:
  - No underline (`text-decoration: none`)
  - Green color on hover (`:hover`)

---

## üìå Submission Instructions:
- File Names: `profile.html`, `colors.html`, `style-practice.html`

